@G__Halliday @criticalgassing For me the key question is WHY this brings staffing below minimum.
If it’s a fully staffed team and several others have already booked leave for that day, then I think it’s not unreasonable to say that they can’t approve the request.
1/2

@K_Walthall I recently saw a comparison* of ED responses vs hospital average for the NHS staff survey. 
It was a really clear demonstration that whilst the whole NHS is under pressure, ED staff are feeling it a lot more than some other areas of the hospital.
* from St. Elsewhere’s

